,Recommended,291860,33464364,Posted: 11 July,all,Špōōkë JaviNiceDay,"Don't let the Early Access status prevent you from dropping a few bucks on this game. As an avid player of Battleblock Theater (On Xbox), it was easy to make the decision to buy. Humorous, diverse, a few secrets and a TON of weapons to find, one of the best soundtracks I've heard in a while, AND comes with a narrator out to make the main protagonist's life hell, Pit People is worth every dollar spent on it, even in it's current Early Access state. It has potential to be an amazing game after the release of the completed version. Speaking of Early Access, if you want it, you better get it now before the price raises for the completed game.As a warning, here's some features and things to consider before you whip out your wallet:-The story is incomplete, so you'll be waiting on that for a bit.-It's not really getting constant updates.-There aren't many City Quests series at the moment; we're standing at about 6, but each one offers it's own challenge, with weapons, gold, and sometimes exclusive fighters as rewards. The dialouge and story for said quests is quite humorous, you'll at one point find yourself recreating what's basically the American Revolution (see 'The R3DC04Ts Are Coming!')-When traversing the world map, there are MANY quests to find and do, they'll usually result in fighting. You'll get juicy rewards from them though!-There is a wide variety of fighters to 'recruit'. Said recruiting is done through killing your target's friends while leaving him alive to watch, then throwing a net at them and stuffing them into a cage not shortly after throwing said net at them.-Also, said fighters can also have some pretty good gear that you can strip from them later and place onto your better fighters, others have overall stupid but funny names, said names are left up to RNGesus to pick.-Once you've made a good, well balanced and well leveled team, you can place them into 'The Pit' to fight to the death against other players in real time via use of a giant space telephone. However, I can say from experience that finding somebody to battle with takes quite a while, so be prepared to wait.Choice is up to you if you want to buy Pit People or not, but I highly recommend you do. Once again, before the price raises after it's completed."
