76561197998454887,Not Recommended,291860,29896133,Posted: 13 February,all,JediMage,"Lets just start with pros. It's funny. And it's pokemon of sorts. It also is a tactical turn-based game, where you need to position your squad well, or face the consequences.Lets get to cons. It should be a game. But as of now, this is just a humor collection (and not the finest one either, let's be honest). This ""game"" horribly lacks one thing, and one thing only: GAMEPLAY. If you pick a character ""A"" and a character ""B"" of the same race, the only difference it will have is their level (and i actually doubt that it even has any significance). You can wear same gear as your other character, so what's the point? And most of the gear has no difference exept the looks. You wanna crush your enemies with golden scepter? Sure. You wanna do it with a lolipop instead? Fine, it matters not. You can even pick the giant ice-cream cone and it will be still as good for crushing your enemies, as the sax or some actual mace (this is somewhat untrue, since really rarely you get the gear with additional effects, like fire resistance, poinsoned attacks and stuff. But still). My biggest porblem as of now is that on the Xth battle you get bored. You probably have same characters as you had X-1 battles before, so you just do the very same thing you did for X-1 battles before, and kill your enemies the very same way you killed them for X-1 battles before. WHY? I had 30 level ups already, can't i be somewhat stronger? Can't i have some new skills to test? The best way to describe this game would be ""like heroes of might and magic, but without heroes, and all you have is your army - which is forever limited to N units per squad"". But if, one day, having 2 cupcakes will mean more than x2 healing. If, one day, having hummie ""A"" will mean something different from having hummie ""B"". If, one day, Horatio will actually DIE. That day will be the day when this game becomes much better than it is now.TBH, i cant say that this game is bad, or good. It is neutral. If you want some funnies, you will find this game better than neutral; If you want to play a game, you will find this game worse than neutral. But i will press the ""not recommended"" button, just for the sake of keeping balance with all those ""recommended"" reviews this game already has. Besides, this is Early Access. The game still has more room for improvement. So lets hope for the best, and watch events unfold."
