76561198025376643,Recommended,291860,29869320,Posted: 12 February,all,Little Phoenix,"If you've kept up with this companies games, you'll know even if you don't like a game you should buy it because the next game tends to benefit from also owning a game.That said, this one fills a niche in Steam that was muh needed to be filled.  Its simple and yet offers a varity of ways to customise fighters.  Some items have 0 effects, while others trade off one benefit for another.  The game is fairly well balanced because of it, with nothing giving you a 0 absolute advantage over another.I would say of the 4 games this company has produced in the years, this is one of the top end of the 4."
,Recommended,291860,29903996,Posted: 13 February,all,Maxwell Sinclair,"The TL;DR Version:I'm only a couple of hours into this game and I've already discovered a Unicorn that doubles as artillery and a pair of gnomes in flying toilets as well as beaten numerous people to a pulp with a giant lollipop. Nuff said.The Actual ReviewThe humor is crude in the most wonderful way and it suits the art style perfectly. Speaking of art style, it's the most adorable looking game I've seen in awhile, it's really dorky in all the right ways and it contrasts beautifully with the over the top violence that is the game. The overworld aspect is a weird mixture of the really old school Final Fantasy and Legend of Zelda games with Pokemon, a lot of people have compared this to pokemon on account of how you recruit new members for your roster.The main villain is one of the best I've seen so far, and right on Par with Dusan from Watchdogs 2 (perhaps a controversial opinion but I really liked him as a villain) and his near constant interference in your affairs will keep you on your toes without being a pain. Not to mention his voice overs. I want to give special mention to the actor who voiced him because he is just wonderful.The music is the other feature of this game that's absolutely stunning, it's an interesting line up of electroblends, from swing to funk and a few others in between, and if you get sick of the music in the city (which is pretty hard to do) you can always find records and unlock new songs to change it too. One of the best features is that the song will remain changed until you change it again, even if you leave the city and come back.Pit People lures you in with it's charming villain, humorous story and adorable art style but make no mistake, it will not be an easy experience. The game is forgiving enough, as death only has consequences up until you return to the town, but the battles can quickly overwhelm you if you're not paying attention and often times you'll find yourself losing fighters without immediately realising why. This game is incredibly fun though and I don't think I could recommend it enough."
,Recommended,291860,29934243,Posted: 14 February,all,hot potatwoah,"This game! Oh boy!Behemoth has done it again, this time they hit what could quite possibly be one of their most engrossing ands fluid experiences. I've owned and played all of their games (excluding Alien Hominid) and have to say, this is easily tied for my favorite of their games.Strategic, fast-paced fun, that's all there is to it. Behemoth's signature quirky style and humor gives this game an edge on other TRPG wannabes on the steam store.A few notes for the Devs though, if they're reading!As of Home Improvement 1, there is no skip turn button in combat. While it's nothing major, it does severely effect the flow of the game for TRPG veterans, or people who understand how the turn will play out. Since movement is fairly.. Slow, due to low movement ranges and large maps, this makes a very tedious experience during overworld encounters, and while most will be fine with it, it'd definitely be a welcome change."
