,Recommended,291860,29345863,Posted: 18 January,all,Brb Hanging Myself,"This is a very fun and simple game, yet it's deep and complex in a unique way.The story is comedical and light hearted which we've come to expect from Behemoth. The dialogues between characters are very humorous and unexpected. Although the story is very short as of now (the game only being in Alpha) the immense amount of side quests and the arena for PvP already gives this game long playability.The combat system is very well implemented, having different characters which are effective against others gives for a very diverse team builder. There is no one way to build your team and it is fun to test out different combinations and see what works.The character customization is a very fun aspect of the game, allowing you to collect, trade and create a very unique looking team. Since most (not all) of the changes in the same catagory affect only the look and not the damage you have no punishment in making your team look as crazy, funny or badass as you want. And I guess i should mention the NPC names... They're amazing. Enough said.Overall, I've been playing this game with a friend throughout, and I can say it is a lot of fun. We are excited for the whole game to come out but are right now content with finishing the many side missions and trying to beat the unfair arena (which by the way, is VERY unfair).I would strongly recommend this game to anyone. It's light hearted, funny and addicting; it's nice to see a game in Alpha that shows so much promise. I'd even go as far to say that if this was the final form of the game I would still spend the money on it.Now if you'll excuse me, I have a unicorn mortar team to make."
