,Recommended,291860,29335491,Posted: 18 January,all,DedSecPony.exe,"Ah yes, Pit People, my new favorite! Even on its unfinished state.THE GAMEThe game is a turn-based RPG strategy with the witty humor and a beautiful cartoonish art style that made me fell in love with The Behemoth's games. Its a simple, yet clear take to Turn-Based Strategies, a genre that I was completely unfamilliar of. You can explore the world tokidnaprecruit other fighters not only because of their stats, but their names too, find more goldMONEYYYYYYand loot, and undertake a LOT of other sidequests other than story mode.(more on that later) The game also has a multikill indicator and its the most satisfying thing ive ever heard.THE STORYAlthough short, it was hilarious! And honestly the very antagonistic narrator (who's VA also voiced the narrator from BBT) that is also a giant space bear is slowly becoming my new favorite bad guy and might even kick Bill Cipher from the TV show Gravity Falls (which is kinda hard tbh) from the ""Best Villan"" pedastal of my heart. The first snippet of the story already features fourth wall-beraking antics, and a really meta narrator that proclamed himselfGodof this post-apocalyptic hex-patterned earth. Plus the fully animated cutscenes are really cool!MUSICThe. Soundtrack. Is. Gud. Pls. Listen. 11/10THINGS I WAS slightly BOTHERED ATSuggestions>It was kinda hard to know what fighter you are currently selecting right now even with my 23-inch monitor on my PCwell then, its been updated to a yellow outline for the selected fighter! It's now eaiser to see what fighter are you currently selecting right now.>the lack of a mac version aaaaaaaa (im aware that a mac verison would come soon tho)>more compatibility with touch screened laptops, so I was able to try the game in a laptop with a touch screen although with a option to include a end turn button on screen (and shaking btw) was a bit helpful, I personally think that it needs a bit more essential controls like canc