76561198107905924,Recommended,291860,33570677,Posted: 15 July,all,Asian Cowboy Ninja Dude,"TL:DR? Charming, Psychotic, and Lemony FreshThe Behemoth once again bring their charming artstyle and unceasably comedic dialogue to the strategy realm, with hints of the team member catching of pokemon, thousands of unit cosmetics with varying functionality seen in every other jrpg, and the afforementioned charm from Battleblock & Castle Crashers.Quests and Characters are spread accross the world that inexplicably want to kill you just for 'almost running them over with your wagon.' Reference after reference is hidden everywhere from the NPCs, to the Areas, and even the occasional hairstyle. You wrap yourself into this world of crazy people as a gang of fanged beasts attempt to destroy all our precious cow painted ten-gallon hats, just to give an example of some of the thing you can encounter (and no I did not make that up.)With the 20 different races to catch (one of them is a clone of another) of varying pros, cons, & strategies entailing them. Each one brings a new set of rules to follow and it's up to you how you want to utilize them in battle as a few are flexible enough to fit different roles. With synergies galore and a new weapon/hat/shield earned after every battle, no one team ever feels the same (unless of course you made it be the same as another team.)One of it's prime features is the thing that the title speaks of, THE PIT, a multiplayer battle arena where you can duke it out 1v1, 2v2, or face 3 waves back-to-back alone or with a friend by your side. With gold cosmetics able to win via the tournament, you'll be able to show off your champions in their new beautiful outfits in no time!The biggest problem with the game atm is that its story is missing, something clearly stated by The Behemoth. Although the multiplayer has been the star of their last two games, the story shed light onto the land's lore and brought it's own crowd of players there for a singleplayer experience. I can't feel truly satisfied with this greatness until I see an end to the story, HOWEVER, the core gameplay mechanics are still enough to bring you to enjoy and play it while still in it's early access. If you want to go through the story in one fell swoop then you should wait til full release, however if you're fine with it's currently unfinished ORDER TODAY!"
,Recommended,291860,34165100,Posted: 11 August,all,It's time to lewd ;v,"So far the game is very funny and charming. The art style is very nice to the eyes, cartoon fits the tone of the game very well. The writing is hilarious and Stamper (the narrator) nails it with this performance. The game hosts a wide variety of characters to ""recruit"" and a plethora of weapons, armour, and shields to equip your people with. The interactions between characters are fun. The story is very fun and is added upon by the interesting characters within the main story and the side story characters are also very well written. Did I mention this game is funny as hell?There are so many more ways I can praise this game, but I'll get to a few problems the game has. 1) I have encountered a few bugs (obviously this is easily fixable) 2) The combat is a bit unusual to me, still. I understand how the combat works it's just I wish I could select who to attack instead of it being decided for me. 3) The overworld, whilst fun, is kinda boring to go across. Now I get it, all games need to have down time to pace things out; but the overworld in this game has some weird hitboxes that makes going across it somewhat annoying. You'll occasionally get stuck on a water tile that you're no where near, for example. One case that I encountered was I couldn't go through a mountain pass (it was a 1 tile wide ""road"" with mountains on both sides) because of the weird hitboxes on the mountains. Though there are several other ways to get to where you're going this still provides a ""*sigh* really?"" moment.These are the problems I've encountered with the game. Now, don't get me wrong, there are SOOOOO many more things to like about this game(I've listed a few in the first paragraph.) Overall I recommend this game to pretty much anyone looking for a fun game or a good strategy game. The equipment system in this game isn't innovative by any means, but they've mastered it and it has some depth to it. I don't like giving ratings but it's a good way to communicate the quality of a game.8.5/10 I would buy it again"
