76561198035890996,Recommended,291860,29476824,Posted: 24 January,all,Legionstone,"A game made by the people who made Castle Crashers and Battleblock theater, comes Pit PeoplePit people is a hexgonal turn-based strategy game, the twist here is that your units attack units on their own free-will, meaning that positioning is extremely important.The art-style is simple but incredibly effective, being extremely colorful, vibrant, and having everything and everyone popout, every item is different in terms of art design and every character is memorable.The gameplay is deceptively simple, but heavily rooted in complicated strategies, team compositions and even gear distribution, luckily, the team at Behemoth were able to make this game pretty easy to learn and play, but difficult to master.My main problem with the game are relatively simple ones, first, the inability to scroll out the map can be problematic sometimes, especially against a full team against a full team, another problem is that the gear that you obtain rarely differ against each other, I would like to have like very small differences, but differences none the less (I want my throwing straws to deal more damage than Yusef's default axes xD)Thirdly, some of the non-human party members are limited in their apperal, I would like that to be changed, it would be awesome to have a whole group of kobolds wearing hats and wielding chicken drums hehe.Besides that, I would reccomend this game for many people, Behemoth fans, hexagon-turn based Strategists, normal people to give this a try, despite it being an early access game, its well polished and no doubt will be absolutely amazing when it finally releases."
