,Recommended,291860,31215117,Posted: 18 April,all,magiks,"tactics rpg with some really interesting twists i haven't seen in the genre before and a pretty strong basis in collectable monsters. i sunk a pretty notable portion of my playtime so far just running around the open world and capturing opponents for their gear or to build new teams, and the gameplay surrounding the constant goal of collecting a lot of dudes is excellent.pit people puts the sorts of elements into the tactics rpg genre that you would expect from the behemoth (battles are super chaotic and♥♥♥♥♥♥explodes constantly, you can't directly influence every single thing your units do to the same degree that you can in other games, etc) and it works shockingly well. i didn't really feel the gameplay (worth noting that this has only been in early access for like 3 months as of this review) growing stagnant, largely because the tone and pace are preeetty casual and laid back most of the time, and battles are visually entertaining enough that things consistently feel interesting and new.the only current downside is the actual story is super dang short, but again, early access, and i believe the next update is focused on story improvements so no big deal there. there's also enough side content to keep you entertained for at least a dozen or two hours, w/ sidequests being available both at your hub and scattered across the world, and the whole appeal of the ""gotta catch em all"" kinda gameplay. the humor can be a bit hit or miss if you aren't into poop jokes, i guess, so that's worth noting. also, i haven't tried the coop or multiplayer in general yet, so i can't weigh in on that.pit people's a promising as hell title though, i rarely play an early access game and immediately feel like i got my money's worth. i'm really excited to see this thing completed."
