76561198014325964,Recommended,291860,29404989,Posted: 21 January,all,JoeWarhost,"Let met start by saying I reccomend this game. The laughs itself is worth the $15. The behemoth always makes pretty good games, and I've known about several of the people involved in this game back in their Newgrounds days over a decade ago. But, I do believe this game has some issues - not counting the incomplete story campaign, which is mentioned in-game by the developers as a work in progress. At the time of writing this, it will only last you about an hour if you try to complete it quickly. But the game also generates random encounters with rewards and ratcheting difficulty, as well as co-op and multiplayer vs.The good:- The game is funny. Really funny.- The strategy is easy to pick up and accessible.- Play with a friend!- Turn-based strategy without the premadeath and nessescary save-scumming that *cough* X-Com still seems to have a hard time getting rid of.- A high degree of customization and collectibles seems to provide a lot of replay value.- A giant world with tons of sidequests and rewards.The bad:- This game has a wierd habit of making the world full of color and life, but making the characters washed out and a little bland. For a capture-the-pokemon style of collection and recruitment, it's weird that most of the combatants are stark white humans in off-white clothes.- The strategy is flat, without elevation, without a variety of terrain bonuses or a huge variety in abilities or defences. Most fights turn into bottlenecking and musical hexes.- Health bars are so huge that often the fights turn into attrition slugfests."
