,Recommended,291860,29388969,Posted: 20 January,all,Spookiux,"Another great game by The Behemoth, this game stays true to Castle Crashers and Battleblock Theatre by keeping the humor and charm of both. This game unlike CC and BT has a lot of replayabilty. You now have the ability to play online which is a lot of fun. At the time of writing this review it is in Early Access I got this game a few days after it came out, played through all the story and side quests and then left it alone. I come back to it and there is more content and you can see how much the Developers care about there game, they take time for well made, content filled updates. The game has many characters that you can capture and get onto your team, if you want a healer that is good, get the penguin with the tuba, if you want long rang attacks get a unicorn. The game also has a lot of customization, you can change your characters to your deight making the game feel like you are controlling it. What I have played of the story so far is amazing, it tells it in a great way but doesn't take long before you are jumping around killing things. This game is another masterpiece by Behemoth and when it gets out of early access it will probably be a must have RPG for any Behemoth fans. 9/10 (needs more buckled pants)"
