,Recommended,291860,33055632,Posted: 30 June,all,Donny,"Pit People, one of the games I was looking forward to for some time, is, at its core, a fun, inventive and hilarious game with some real depth to it's gameplay. The graphics are bright and appealing, the music, sound and voice acting (take a bow Stamper) are excellent, crisp and fitting and the atmosphere and humour is highly amusing, resulting in one of those rare instances where I find myself laughing out loud whilst I playThe negatives, few as they are, barely upset this high trend. The game can be a little confusing at times, lack of information or a tutorial outside of basic combat can be a tad frustrating and online battles tend to be extremely one sided as some players who are a higher level, and having farmed the best weapons and characters, will crush those that barely know anything about the game. The biggest offender of this was when I came up against someone three times my level with the best gear and enemies in his roster. Turned out, they had clocked in a couple hundred hours of the game where as I had clocked in a miserable five.That point aside, this game is still highly enjoyable and fun and, a must for those of Stamper especially.88/100"
